---
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<section
  id="hero"
  class="relative flex min-h-screen flex-col items-center justify-center overflow-hidden px-6 py-24 text-center sm:px-10"
>
  <div
    aria-hidden="true"
    class="absolute left-1/2 top-1/2 -z-10 h-[480px] w-[480px] -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 rounded-full bg-[#7c3aed] opacity-20 blur-3xl"
  >
  </div>
  <div
    aria-hidden="true"
    class="absolute inset-0 -z-20 bg-[radial-gradient(circle_at_center,rgba(124,58,237,0.08),#0d0d14_70%)]"
  >
  </div>

  <img
    src={`${base}/logo.png`}
    alt="CrewRig"
    width="240"
    height="131"
    class="mb-10 h-16 w-auto sm:h-20"
    loading="eager"
    data-aos="fade-down"
  />

  <h1
    class="max-w-4xl text-3xl font-bold leading-tight tracking-tight text-[#f0f0f6] sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl"
    data-aos="fade-up"
  >
    Your AI knows you. It has no idea who your team is.
  </h1>

  <p
    class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg text-[#9090a8] sm:text-xl"
    data-aos="fade-up"
    data-aos-delay="100"
  >
    CrewRig is the shared layer your AI tools have been missing — versioned
    prompts, skills, and personas your whole team inherits. Stop reinventing
    context every standup.
  </p>

  <div
    class="mt-10 flex flex-col items-center gap-4 sm:flex-row"
    data-aos="fade-up"
    data-aos-delay="200"
  >
    <a
      href="https://github.com/hcross/crewrig"
      class="inline-flex min-h-[44px] items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-[#7c3aed] px-6 py-3 font-semibold text-white shadow-lg shadow-[#7c3aed]/30 transition hover:bg-[#8b5cf6]"
    >
      Fork on GitHub →
    </a>
    <a
      href="#quick-start"
      class="inline-flex min-h-[44px] items-center justify-center rounded-lg border border-[#7c3aed]/40 px-6 py-3 font-semibold text-[#f0f0f6] transition hover:border-[#8b5cf6] hover:bg-[#7c3aed]/10"
    >
      Quick Start ↓
    </a>
  </div>

  <p
    class="mt-10 text-sm uppercase tracking-widest text-[#9090a8]"
    data-aos="fade-up"
    data-aos-delay="300"
  >
    Open source · Works with Claude Code &amp; Gemini CLI
  </p>
</section>
